# Templates are shipped verbatim into a user's project, so their line endings are
# a product decision, not an editor preference. 18 of them were once committed as
# CRLF, which put a stray `\r` at the end of every generated line — invisible
# trailing whitespace in every scaffolded file.
#
# `eol=lf` forces LF in the working tree on every platform, including Windows, so
# a contributor's editor cannot reintroduce it. (The generator also normalizes at
# render time — this keeps the source clean too.)
*.ejs text eol=lf

# Generated-project sources and configs: same reasoning.
*.ts    text eol=lf
*.json  text eol=lf
*.yml   text eol=lf
*.md    text eol=lf
